  "prompt": "What is the most depressing song?",
  "response": "Depression is subjective and can be triggered by different things for different people. Some songs that are often cited as particularly sad or depressing include:\n\n1. \"Hurt\" by Nine Inch Nails, also famously covered by Johnny Cash.\n2. \"Tears in Heaven\" by Eric Clapton.\n3. \"Creep\" by Radiohead.\n4. \"Everybody Hurts\" by R.E.M.\n5. \"Mad World\" by Gary Jules (originally by Tears for Fears).\n6. \"Nothing Compares 2 U\" by Sin\u00e9ad O'Connor.\n7. \"Fast Car\" by Tracy Chapman.\n\nThese songs are often noted for their somber tones and melancholic lyrics, which can evoke feelings of sadness or melancholy in listeners.",
